-- P&G’s Diamond Deal Needs ‘Favorable’ Probe Resolution
-- B y   L a u r e n   C o l e m a n - L o c h n e r
-- 2011-12-15T19:25:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-15/p-g-s-diamond-deal-depends-on-favorable-resolution-of-probes.html
(Corrects agency’s name in first paragraph.)  Procter & Gamble Co. (PG)  said the sale
of its Pringles business to  Diamond Foods Inc. (DMND)  depends on the
“favorable resolution” of an internal accounting investigation
and a U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission probe.  “Our commitment to this transaction is predicated on the
favorable resolution of all these current investigations,” Paul
Fox, a Procter & Gamble spokesman, said in an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Callan at 
 jcallan2@bloomberg.net  